[Article in Chinese]

Lu XH(1), Pu CQ, Huang XS, Mao YL, Liu JX, Luo P.

Author information:
(1)Department of Neurology, General Hospital of PLA, Beijing 100853, China. 
brightxh@sina.com

OBJECTIVE: To compare the clinical, pathological, laboratory test and follow-up 
data between familial and sporadic patients with distal myopathy with rimmed 
vacuoles (DMRV) and discuss the characteristics of this disorder in Chinese 
population.
METHODS: The clinical and pathological features, laboratory data and follow-up 
results of 33 sporadic and 4 familial cases of pathologically confirmed DMRV 
were summarized and compared retrospectively.
