groups. The disease was slowly progressive and severely affected the quality of 
life of the patients, but did not produce obvious effect on the life expectancy.
CONCLUSION: The clinical, pathological and laboratory data of Chinese DMRV 
patients are basically similar to those of Japanese cases. Sporadic cases tend 
to show more dysmorphic features than the familial ones, and occasional sporadic 
cases have early disease onset in early childhood.

