population doubling levels) of Hs68 cells. In contrast, DHEA at non-cytotoxic 
concentrations (≤50 μM) did not significantly affect NAD(+) levels, SIRT1 
activities or the lifespan of Hs68 cells. These results suggest that 2-DG 
extends the lifespan of Hs68 cells by increased NAD(+) levels and SIRT1 
activities, and that 2-DG has a potential as a CR mimetic.

